    <title>EHSFIT: Finding Your Passion </title>
    <link>http://ehstoday.com/blog/ehsfit-finding-your-passion</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;node-body blog-body&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Staying active in cooler temperatures and avoiding cabin fever can be quite the challenge. For me, it&amp;rsquo;s always a balance between the cold and precipitation this time of year. It&amp;rsquo;s not much different than assessing risk in the workplace.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I always ask a set of questions: What is the temperature? If it is between 30&amp;deg;F and 40&amp;deg;F, what are the conditions of the trails in the park? Is there ice? Are the roads and sidewalks clear? What clothing do I need to keep my skin and body protected?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

