    <title>Making Value-Based Medical Care Work in an Occupational Setting</title>
    <link>http://ehstoday.com/health/making-value-based-medical-care-work-occupational-setting</link>
    <description>
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-byline&quot;&gt;

        
        
                
                By Greg Vanichkachorn, M.D. 
                
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;div class=&quot;field-deck&quot;&gt;

        
        
                
                Occupational physicians can and should use evidence-based care to improve outcomes for employees while reducing risk and costs for employers.
                
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;node-body article-body&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;The U.S. healthcare system has undergone significant changes over the years. One transformation that likely will stand the test of time is the industry&amp;#39;s transition from fee-for-service to value-based care payment models, which helps reduce cost while improving quality.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


