    <link>http://ehstoday.com/safety/osha-fines-cm-truck-beds-535411-two-dozen-violations</link>
    <description>

    &lt;div class=&quot;field-deck&quot;&gt;

        
        
                
                Agency discovers trucking company failed to provide respirator fit tests, machine guards, welding protection and did not properly label chemicals.
                
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;node-body article-body&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;OSHA recently discovered two dozen violations at BigTex Trailer Manufacturing Inc. after a complaint of unsafe working conditions at the company.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oklahoma-based BigTex Trailer Manufacturing Inc., which operates as CM Truck Beds, racked up $535, 411 in fines for 20 serious violations, one willful and three repeated violations.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


