    <title>The Future of Lockout/Tagout: Is Zero Risk an Outdated Approach?</title>
    <link>http://ehstoday.com/safety/future-lockouttagout-zero-risk-outdated-approach</link>
    <description>

    &lt;div class=&quot;field-deck&quot;&gt;

        
        
                
                The ANSI/ASSE Z244.1 Standard is considered the defining document for addressing the complex issues of lockout/tagout and methods for the control of hazardous energy, and the Z244 Committee is moving in a new direction.
                
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;node-body article-body&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;The control of hazardous energy in the workplace continues to be a challenge for many employers. According to OSHA, failure to control hazardous energy accounts for nearly 10 percent of the serious accidents in many industries.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://ehstoday.com/safety/future-lockouttagout-zero-risk-outdated-approach&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
