    <title>Are Your Top Leaders Engaged in Driving Safety Performance?</title>
    <link>http://ehstoday.com/safety-leadership/are-your-top-leaders-engaged-driving-safety-performance</link>
    <description>
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-byline&quot;&gt;

        
        
                
                By Len Jannaman
                
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;div class=&quot;field-deck&quot;&gt;

        
        
                
                Savvy corporations recognize the importance of having top leadership teams engaged in driving safety performance. So how can you engage your corporate leaders?
                
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;node-body article-body&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;In a perfect world, everybody does the right thing, the right way, all the time, for the right reasons, on the road to zero injuries and incidents. But unfortunately, we don&amp;#39;t live in a perfect world and injuries often do happen. And when they do, while the financial impact can be crippling, the human costs are much greater.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://ehstoday.com/safety-leadership/are-your-top-leaders-engaged-driving-safety-performance&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
