    <title>Department of Labor Files Suit Against Jasper Roofing Contractors Inc. for Terminating Employee</title>
    <link>http://ehstoday.com/safety/department-labor-files-suit-against-jasper-roofing-contractors-inc-terminating-employee-0</link>
    <description>

    &lt;div class=&quot;field-deck&quot;&gt;

        
        
                
                Safety manager at Jasper Roofing terminated for cooperating with OSHA inspection.
                
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;node-body article-body&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;A lawsuit filed by the U.S. Department of Labor just before year-end alleges that Jasper Roofing Contractors Inc. fired a safety manager for complying with an OSHA inspection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The suit is the result of an investigation by OSHA&amp;#39;s Whistleblower Protection Program.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://ehstoday.com/safety/department-labor-files-suit-against-jasper-roofing-contractors-inc-terminating-employee-0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
